---
import StaticArticlePage from '@/components/ui/StaticArticlePage.astro'
---

<StaticArticlePage
  description="A plain-language explanation of what SeniorPath stores and what third parties may receive."
  kicker="Legal"
  title="Privacy Policy"
>
  <h2>What SeniorPath stores in your browser</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath currently uses browser storage for a small amount of product state: your locale preference and the
    guide-completion markers used by the site UI. That data stays in your browser on that device until you clear
    it.
  </p>

  <h2>Traffic measurement</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath may use Cloudflare Web Analytics for lightweight site-level measurement, such as pageviews, top
    pages, and referrers. The goal is to understand aggregate traffic and what content is being read, not to build
    ad profiles or personalized tracking around individual visitors.
  </p>
  <p>
    Analytics configuration and data handling for that service are governed by Cloudflare's own terms and privacy
    policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Comments on articles</h2>
  <p>
    Some article pages may load Giscus for comments. If comments are enabled and you interact with them, the page
    will load resources from Giscus and GitHub, and your use of that comment system will be governed by their
    policies as well.
  </p>

  <h2>External links</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath may link to outside articles, tools, or reference material. When you leave the site or interact
    with embedded third-party services, those services may collect data under their own policies.
  </p>

  <h2>What SeniorPath does not currently do</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath does not currently run a public account system, checkout flow, or newsletter form on the site. If
    that changes in the future, this page should be updated to explain what new data is collected and why.
  </p>

  <h2>Updates</h2>
  <p>
    This policy may be revised as the product changes. Material updates should be reflected on this page so the
    site's actual behavior stays aligned with the text here.
  </p>
</StaticArticlePage>
